

                              Abrams Tank Simulator
                                  Documentation



    F1 = Gunners View (and firing control panel).
    F2 = Map and Navigators View. *
    F3 = View from the top (Opening atop of tank).
    F4 = Drives View.
    F5 = Toggle Sound.

    * F7 - F10 are used only when you using F2.

     F7 = Look forward.
     F8 = Look right.
     F9 = Look behind.
    F10 = Look left.

    1 = Main gun firing shell HEAT.
            The HEAT shell is classified as a High Explosive Anti-Tank Shell.

    2 = Main gun firing shell SABBOT.
            Armor-Piercing Shell.

    3 = Main gun firing shell AX.
            This shell is much like a missile, used for Anti-Chopper and
            Anti-Armor uses, mainly long distance.

    ESC = Pause.
        Q = Quit game.
        T = Toggle Night Vision (Use at night and/or when you are surrounded by
                    smoke.
        A = Return turret to same heading as main tank.
        L = Make turret lock on to selected target.
    Enter = Have computer lock on to target & Target ID.
        Z = Zoom in (1X, 5X, 10X)
        C = Toggles between maneuvering tank unit and moving turret separately.
        M = Use machine gun.
    Space = Fire Main Gun

    Arrow Keys:

    Control your direction and speed, you'll figure this out after 10 or so
    minutes.

